Ghiles in London.
The meeting was boycotted by Algeria's main political parties, including the
lay Front des Forces Socialistes, led by Mr Hocine Ait Ahmed, and the former
ruling Front de Liberation National Party. Both urged Algerian leaders to
open negotiations with the banned Islamic Salvation Front which was poised
